<subSubSection id="799455F9FFF5FF9EFF20957BFAF1FE48" pageId="1" pageNumber="595" type="discussion">
7. In conclusion, 
<taxonomicName id="F68E7DF1FFF5FF9EFE32957BFD2FFE8F" authority="Peters, 1871" authorityName="Peters" authorityYear="1871" box="[389,660,300,326]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Dasypterus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="595" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="03FADA60FFF5FF9EFE32957BFDBEFE8C" box="[389,517,300,325]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="595">Dasypterus</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="551F7B83FFF5FF9EFDBC957BFD2FFE8F" author="Peters, W." box="[523,660,300,326]" pageId="1" pageNumber="595" pagination="900 - 914" refId="ref1689" refString="Peters, W. (1871) Eine monographische Ubersicht der Chiropterengattungen Nycteris und Atalapha. Monatsberichte der Koniglich Preussischen Akademie der Wissenschaften zu Berlin, 1870, 900 - 914, 1 pl." type="journal article" year="1871">Peters, 1871</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
has priority over 
<taxonomicName id="F68E7DF1FFF5FF9EFCE0957BFBD5FE8F" authority="Reuter, 1872" authorityName="Reuter" authorityYear="1872" box="[855,1134,300,326]" class="Insecta" family="Anthocoridae" genus="Dasypterus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="595" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="03FADA60FFF5FF9EFCE0957BFC6CFE8C" box="[855,983,300,325]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="595">Dasypterus</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="551F7B83FFF5FF9EFC6B957BFBD5FE8F" author="Reuter, O. M." box="[988,1134,300,326]" pageId="1" pageNumber="595" pagination="557 - 567" refId="ref1796" refString="Reuter, O. M. (1872) Acanthiidae americanae. Ofversigt af Kongliga Svenska Vetenskaps-Akademiens Forhandlingar, 28 (5), 557 - 567." type="journal article" year="1872">Reuter, 1872</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, rendering Reuter’s name a junior homonym (
<bibRefCitation id="551F7B83FFF5FF9EFE1B951EFD8AFEAA" author="ICZN &amp; International Commission on Zoological Nomenclature" box="[428,561,329,355]" pageId="1" pageNumber="595" refId="ref1554" refString="ICZN [International Commission on Zoological Nomenclature] (1999) International Code of Zoological Nomenclature. 4 th Edition. The International Trust for Zoological Nomenclature, London, 306 pp." type="book" year="1999">ICZN 1999</bibRefCitation>
, Art. 53.2, 56), here rejected. There are no available synonyms for 
<taxonomicName id="F68E7DF1FFF5FF9EFAAA951DFECDFE49" authority="Reuter, 1872" authorityName="Reuter" authorityYear="1872" class="Insecta" family="Anthocoridae" genus="Dasypterus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="595" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="03FADA60FFF5FF9EFAAA951DFA26FEAA" box="[1309,1437,330,355]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="595">Dasypterus</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="551F7B83FFF5FF9EFF559530FECDFE49" author="Reuter, O. M." box="[226,374,358,385]" pageId="1" pageNumber="595" pagination="557 - 567" refId="ref1796" refString="Reuter, O. M. (1872) Acanthiidae americanae. Ofversigt af Kongliga Svenska Vetenskaps-Akademiens Forhandlingar, 28 (5), 557 - 567." type="journal article" year="1872">Reuter, 1872</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, and a new replacement name is required under Art. 60 (
<bibRefCitation id="551F7B83FFF5FF9EFC4B9531FB3FFE49" author="ICZN &amp; International Commission on Zoological Nomenclature" box="[1020,1156,358,384]" pageId="1" pageNumber="595" refId="ref1554" refString="ICZN [International Commission on Zoological Nomenclature] (1999) International Code of Zoological Nomenclature. 4 th Edition. The International Trust for Zoological Nomenclature, London, 306 pp." type="book" year="1999">ICZN 1999</bibRefCitation>
). Thus, I propose
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="799455F9FFF5FF9EFAE59531FE22FE57" pageId="1" pageNumber="595" type="nomenclature">
<taxonomicName id="F68E7DF1FFF5FF9EFAE59531FE9BFE54" authority="Swanson, 2019" authorityName="Swanson" authorityYear="2019" class="Insecta" family="Anthocoridae" genus="Dasyleistes" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="595" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus" taxonStatus="nom. nov.">
<emphasis id="03FADA60FFF5FF9EFAE59531FE9BFE54" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="595">Dasyleistes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="03FADA60FFF5FF9EFE9195D3FE22FE57" bold="true" box="[294,409,388,414]" pageId="1" pageNumber="595">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="18C9671BFFF5FF9EFE9195D3FE22FE57" box="[294,409,388,414]" pageId="1" pageNumber="595">nom. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="799455F9FFF5FF9EFE2895D3FD5BFE57" box="[415,736,388,414]" pageId="1" pageNumber="595" type="reference_group">
for 
<taxonomicName id="F68E7DF1FFF5FF9EFE7295D3FD67FE57" authority="Reuter, 1872" authorityName="Reuter" authorityYear="1872" box="[453,732,388,414]" class="Insecta" family="Anthocoridae" genus="Dasypterus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="595" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="03FADA60FFF5FF9EFE7295D3FDFEFE54" box="[453,581,388,413]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="595">Dasypterus</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="551F7B83FFF5FF9EFDFD95D3FD67FE57" author="Reuter, O. M." box="[586,732,388,414]" pageId="1" pageNumber="595" pagination="557 - 567" refId="ref1796" refString="Reuter, O. M. (1872) Acanthiidae americanae. Ofversigt af Kongliga Svenska Vetenskaps-Akademiens Forhandlingar, 28 (5), 557 - 567." type="journal article" year="1872">Reuter, 1872</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
.
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="799455F9FFF5FF9EFD5295D3FB7DFDF9" pageId="1" pageNumber="595" type="discussion">
The new name is derived from the Greek adjective δασύς, -εῖα, -ύ, Latinized 
<emphasis id="03FADA60FFF5FF9EFEC195F6FE0FFE72" box="[374,436,417,443]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="595">dasys</emphasis>
, 
<emphasis id="03FADA60FFF5FF9EFE7695F6FE45FE72" box="[449,510,417,443]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="595">dasia</emphasis>
, 
<emphasis id="03FADA60FFF5FF9EFDBC95F6FD85FE72" box="[523,574,417,443]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="595">dasy</emphasis>
(combining form 
<emphasis id="03FADA60FFF5FF9EFCBE95F6FC87FE72" box="[777,828,417,443]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="595">dasy</emphasis>
-), ‘with a shaggy surface, hairy’ and the Greek masculine noun λῃστής, Latinized 
<emphasis id="03FADA60FFF5FF9EFDAB95E9FDD9FE11" box="[540,610,446,472]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="595">leistes</emphasis>
, ‘robber, pirate’. The name was chosen to parallel 
<bibRefCitation id="551F7B83FFF5FF9EFB2695E9FA84FE11" author="Reuter, O. M." box="[1169,1343,446,472]" pageId="1" pageNumber="595" pagination="557 - 567" refId="ref1796" refString="Reuter, O. M. (1872) Acanthiidae americanae. Ofversigt af Kongliga Svenska Vetenskaps-Akademiens Forhandlingar, 28 (5), 557 - 567." type="journal article" year="1872">Reuter’s (1872)</bibRefCitation>
original name, in part, by retaining the initial root. The ultimate root was chosen to highlight a common name of these insects, i.e., minute pirate bugs, and to intentionally utilize the same gender as Reuter’s original name. Thus, the new name is masculine and retains the 
<typeStatus id="EE35B8D0FFF5FF9EFD7F9640FD43FDF8" box="[712,760,535,561]" pageId="1" pageNumber="595">type</typeStatus>
species 
<taxonomicName id="F68E7DF1FFF5FF9EFCEE9641FB7DFDF9" authority="Stal, 1860" authorityName="Stal" authorityYear="1860" box="[857,1222,533,560]" class="Insecta" family="Anthocoridae" genus="Xylocoris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="595" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="limbatellus">
<emphasis id="03FADA60FFF5FF9EFCEE9641FBF3FDF9" box="[857,1096,534,560]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="595">Xylocoris limbatellus</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="551F7B83FFF5FF9EFBE69642FB7DFDF9" author="Stal, C." box="[1105,1222,533,560]" pageId="1" pageNumber="595" pagination="1 - 84" refId="ref1881" refString="Stal, C. (1860) Bidrag till Rio Janeiro-traktens Hemipter-fauna. Kongliga Svenska Vetenskaps-Akademiens Handlingar, 2 (7), 1 - 84." type="journal article" year="1860">Stål, 1860</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="799455F9FFF5FF9EFB709641FE10FD41" pageId="1" pageNumber="595" type="synonymic_list">
. This treatment results in four new combinations: 
